Trie

Class TrieNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • Trie.TrieNode

  • public class TrieNode
extends java.lang.Object
    TrieNode class is the nodes in the `trie` data structure implementation. Each node (TrieNode) has the usual two standard fields: a character symbol and a reference to the next TrieNodes. In addition it also has a Node field which has use for the LZ78 algorithm implementation. For normal usage this field can be safely passed as null.
    Author:
    Harshit Maheshwari
